    "e_p0pcesdw2fwmza": {
      "id": "e_p0pcesdw2fwmza",
      "kind": "settlement",
      "name": "Westcliff",
      "fields": {},
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "statblock",
          "name": "Westcliff",
          "meta": "Town · pop. 3352",
          "sections": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "label": "At First Glance",
              "text": "Restrictive Atmosphere: Stringent laws and regulations create a restrictive and controlled environment for the people."
            },
            {
              "type": "keyValue",
              "pairs": [
                {
                  "key": "Government",
                  "value": "Gerontocracy — “The ruling power is held by a council of elderly individuals esteemed for their wisdom and experience.” The archetype of a gerontocracy is a form of government where the ruling power is vested in a council of elderly individuals who are considered to be the most experienced and wise members of society. In this system, decision-making and leadership positions are predominantly held by older adults based on their age and perceived wisdom. (Compare: No modern examples, mostly a tribalistic belief.) Leadership: Matriarch Isadora Swiftwing - The wise and compassionate leader, ensuring the welfare of the citizens and fostering unity. State goals: Prioritizing Collective Well-being - Placing the welfare of the community above individual interests. / Empowering Youth Leadership - Encouraging and mentoring young leaders to ensure a seamless transition of power. Methods: Educational Outreach - Providing opportunities for lifelong learning and educational programs for citizens. / Long-Term Planning Initiatives - Implementing strategies that prioritize the nation's future welfare and stability. The citizenry wants: Promoting Respect for Elders - Demonstrating reverence and appreciation for the wisdom of elderly leaders. Complication: Reliance on Historical Wisdom - Past solutions might not be applicable to current challenges, leading to inefficacy."
                },
                {
                  "key": "Morale",
                  "value": "Neutral Morale: The general sentiment is neither positive nor negative, and people are indifferent to political affairs."
                },
                {
                  "key": "Economy",
                  "value": "Chaos Barter System: A volatile and unpredictable economic system where chaos-aligned beings trade enigmatic artifacts, chaotic energy, and rare dimensional items. Wealth: Free Market Capitalism: An economic policy promoting minimal government intervention, leading to varying wealth distribution based on individual success. Taxes: Potion Ingredients Tariff: Taxing the import and export of rare potion ingredients and magical components. Treasury: Drained: The treasury has been heavily depleted, struggling to meet even essential expenses."
                },
                {
                  "key": "Trade",
                  "value": "Magical Potions: The country is a hub for alchemists who produce potent magical potions, which are exported for various purposes. Chief export: Krakenwood Timber: Wood from the Krakenwood trees found on remote islands, used in crafting items that grant control over water creatures. Luxury trade: Extravagant Clothing: Lavish and opulent clothing made from the finest fabrics, worn by the nobility."
                },
                {
                  "key": "Cuisine",
                  "value": "Floating Isles' Fruits: Exotic fruits harvested from floating islands, known for their light and airy taste."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "label": "Trouble Brewing",
              "text": "Complacency and Entitlement: Citizens may become complacent and entitled, taking the utopian society for granted."
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "label": "Behind Closed Doors",
              "text": "Revolutionary Movements: The country secretly supports or funds revolutionary groups in other nations to destabilize them."
            }
          ],
          "id": "b_vqjiafep"
        }
      ],
      "rev": 1,
      "created": "2026-07-13T00:43:48.073Z",
